IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO WORK FOR THE PRESERVATION AND ENHANCEMENT OF HEALTH FOR CITIZENS OF SOUTHERN ILLINOIS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE PRIMARY MEDICAL AND DENTAL HEALTHCARE.
IRS990.Desc: FEDERALLY QUALIFIED RURAL HEALTH CLINIC - PROVIDES QUALITY PRIMARY HEALTHCARE, DENTAL SERVICES AND PHARMACY REGARDLESS OF RACE, CREED, SEX, NATIONAL ORIGIN, HANDICAP, AGE, OR ABILITY TO PAY TO UNDERSERVED RURAL COMMUNITIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: SHAWNEE ALLIANCE FOR SENIORS PROGRAMS - SHAWNEE ALLIANCE CARE COORDINATORS HELP OLDER ADULTS AND THEIR CAREGIVERS CONNECT TO SERVICES AVAILABLE IN THE COMMUNITY WHICH ENABLE THEM TO MAINTAIN THEIR INDEPENDENCE. CARE COORDINATORS MAKE HOME VISITS TO EVALUATE THE OLDER ADULTS' ABILITY TO FUNCTION INDEPENDENTLY. THE EVALUATION IS COMPREHENSIVE AND PROVIDES THE CARE COORDINATORS WITH INFORMATION NEEDED TO ADVISE THE OLDER ADULT AND THEIR CAREGIVER ON PROGRAMS AND SERVICES AVAILABLE TO MEET THEIR NEEDS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD OF DIRECTORS WERE GIVEN A COPY OF THE 990 FOR THEIR REVIEW AND APPROVAL AT THE BOARD MEETING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SHAWNEE REQUIRES THAT ALL DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, COMMITTEE MEMBERS AND CANDIDATES FOR BOARD SEATS DISCLOSE IN WRITING, AND UPDATE THE WRITTEN DISCLOSURE IF CONDITIONS CHANGE, BUSINESS AND FAMILY RELATIONSHIPS WHICH WOULD CREATE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST AND, WHERE APPLICABLE, PROVIDE A STATEMENT SUGGESTING HOW SUCH CONFLICT COULD BE AVOIDED OR MITIGATED. IN ORDER TO FACILITATE SUCH FULL DISCLOSURE, SHAWNEE REQUIRES DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, AND COMMITTEE MEMBERS TO COMPLETE A DISCLOSURE FORM. COMPLETION OF A DISCLOSURE FORM DOES NOT RELIEVE INDIVIDUALS OF THE OBLIGATION TO COMPLY WITH THESE STANDARDS OF CONDUCT WITH REGARD TO CONFLICTS THAT OCCUR AFTER THE FILING OF THE DISCLOSURE FORM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WILL REVIEW THE CEO'S PERFORMANCE, REVIEW SALARY SURVEYS AND DOCUMENT ALL STAGES OF THE REVIEW PROCESS. THESE ARE PERFORMED BY THE GOVERNANCE COMMITTEE AND THE FULL BOARD HAS INPUT ABILITY. THE CEO WILL REVIEW THE CFO'S PERFORMANCE AND COMPARABLE DATA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, POLICIES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
